The German top-flight league Bundesliga is set to return on May 15th after the government gave the ‘green light’. Bundesliga is keen to finish its season with a number of clubs having resumed training. The league has taken severe measures that will be put up to ensure players’ health while upholding social distancing even during matches. According to reports, the Government is set to give the green light to return on May 15th. READ ALSO:   Premier League clubs prepare for 2020/21 season behind closed doors Bundesliga is set to resume its matches under strict conditions without fans in stadiums with the state premiers expected to give the green light for large shops to reopen probably from May 11th. The top-flight season was suspended in March with nine games left to play for most of the clubs in the division